{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JUytFr9MrFqiAAtuXUy2eP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of what was found and what the script does:\n\n**Non-default configuration catalogued:**\n\n| Category | Item | Detail |\n|---|---|---|\n| Vhosts | `/app`, `/ops` | Non-default (only `/` ships by default) |\n| Users | `app-user`, `ops-user` | Both `management` tag; non-default |\n| Policy | `ha-all` on `/app` | HA mirroring, all queues, `ha-mode=all`, `ha-sync-mode=automatic` |\n| Permissions | `app-user→/app`, `ops-user→/ops` | Full `.*,.*,.*` on each |\n| Queues | `app-queue` (in `/app`), `ops-queue` (in `/ops`) | Classic, durable |\n\n**Rollback script (`rollback.sh`) is a 7-step ordered teardown:**\n1. Clear `ha-all` policy from `/app`\n2. Delete `app-queue` from `/app`\n3. Delete `ops-queue` from `/ops`\n4. Clear `app-user` permissions on `/app`\n5. Clear `ops-user` permissions on `/ops`\n6. Delete users `app-user` and `ops-user`\n7. Delete vhosts `/app` and `/ops`\n\nThe ordering matters — queues and permissions are removed before their vhosts are deleted, and users are cleared after their permissions are gone. The `admin` user and default `/` vhost are left untouched.\n\nThe **`rollback-rehearsal` ConfigMap is created**, the cluster configuration is **verified unchanged** (all three vhosts, all three users, and the `ha-all` policy are still present)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1066,"cache_read_input_tokens":36743,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1066},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"285223cd-7b47-46d3-be15-81d04e6a6a04","uuid":"5804ad39-e084-40fd-b957-e2bab967564e","request_id":"req_011CcQ5KqTp2Fcqq3X6eTggj"}
